import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of the S&P 500 index over the given time period?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data = data.set_index('date')
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.lineplot(data=data, x=data.index, y='price')
    ax.fill_between(data.index, data['price'] - data['daily_return'].std(), data['price'] + data['daily_return'].std(), alpha=0.3)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the volatility of the S&P 500 index over the given time period?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
